name: Key Information Systems
overview:
Key Information Systems, Inc., a technology company, specializes in solutions for corporate infrastructure, business continuity, and storage in the western United States. It offers servers, as well as storage solutions, such as tape storage solutions, backup and information systems, and virtual tape libraries. The company also provides software solutions, such as VMware datacenter and desktop software; Tivoli solutions; WebSphere middleware; DB/2 information management database software; Rational software; FileNet enterprise content management systems; Lotus solutions; and Microsoft technologies. In addition, it offers security solutions, including threat analysis, intrusion detection, Sarbanes-Oxley, payment card industry compliance, desktop security, and IBM managed security. Further, the company provides analysis and performance services, architecture and design services, system implementation services, business continuity services, data center services, and support and maintenance services. Furthermore, it offers virtualization solutions, optimization and infrastructure solutions, business continuity solutions, and business intelligent solutions. The company serves retail and distribution, finance and insurance, education and government, healthcare, media and entertainment, technology, and transportation industries.

Key Information Systems, Inc. was founded in 1995 and is based in Woodland Hills, California with additional offices in Phoenix, Arizona, as well as San Francisco and Newport Beach.
